    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-14T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-14T14:00:00-05:00" n="733"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d733">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">363q116/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Vice Consul at Lourengo Marques, Mozambique</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stanton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-14T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 14, 1930—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Department’s instruction of November 8, 1929, concerning recent
                    legislation affecting religious missions in Mozambique, please take up again
                    with the Governor General in the sense of Department’s instruction above
                    referred to, page two, and report to Department.</p>
                <p>A communication has been received from the Foreign Missions Conference of North
                    America enclosing a memorandum for presentation to the Portuguese Government at
                    Lisbon, a copy of which is being sent to you under cover of transmitting
                        despatch.<note n="24" xml:id="d733fn24">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
